content.text:
The claim says an average score of 9.0 is "unimpressive compared to typical expert contributors." This is a **subjective** judgment — "unimpressive" is a value judgment. The database can confirm the factual part (the average score is indeed 9.0), but whether that score is "unimpressive" is a subjective assessment.

Let me also check where 9.0 falls in the overall distribution to understand the context better:

input.command: sqlite3 "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/codebase_community.sqlite" "SELECT COUNT(*) as users_above_9, (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT u2.Id) FROM posts p2 JOIN users u2 ON p2.OwnerUserId = u2.Id) as total_users FROM (SELECT u.Id, AVG(p.Score) as avg_score FROM posts p JOIN users u ON p.OwnerUserId = u.Id GROUP BY u.Id HAVING avg_score > 9.0) t;"
